    "summary": "H0 NOT falsified by the letter of the pre-reg: criterion C1 (within-grade SHAP-DTI dispersion on the grading surrogate g) fires on 3/3 vintages. C2 (within-grade DTI rank) and C3 (DTI dependence materiality) fail everywhere \u2014 the read-outs a validator most relies on are silent. The disambiguation (post-hoc): C1's within-grade SHAP-DTI ranking tracks realized default on 3/3 vintages, so C1's firing is a real recovery of the consequential structure. C5 (the steelman, on the realized-default model f) is not independent of building the refinement model the stratification test stands in for. Net: the stratification test directly quantifies the consequence (significant within-grade realized-default gaps), needs no surrogate, and ties to the documented policy vocabulary; SHAP-on-g gets there too via C1 but only with a faithful-enough surrogate and the right read-out."
